radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 1.6 cm, fluid filled with a hyperenhancing wall; associated fat stranding in the right lower quadrant. No evidence of abscess or perforation. The visualized heart, lung bases, liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, and intraabdominal large bowel are unremarkable. No free fluid, free air, or lymphadenopathy within the abdomen or pelvis. Mild atherosclerotic calcifications of the intraabdominal aorta. Mild degenerative changes in the thoracic spine.
